Pre-Game Insights: Libya head into the match with solid defensive performances and a notable upturn in performance under new manager Milutin Micho Sredojevic.
Rwanda, under manager Torsten Spittler, have been strong defensively, conceding only one goal in their last six matches.
Both teams have experienced improvements under their new managers and are carrying solid form into the match.
Libya and Rwanda have faced each other eight times, with Libya holding a 5-1 advantage in head-to-head results.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is part of Group D of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
Libya have reached the main draw three times, last in the 2011-12 tournament, while Rwanda have only made it once, back in 2003-04.
Others: Libya's possible starting lineup includes Ali Yousef, Magdy Artiba, and Abdelaziz Ali.
Rwanda's possible starting lineup features Bonheur Mugisha, Thierry Manzi, and Arthur Gitego.
